The '''John Sherman Cooper Power Station''' is a [[coal-fired power plant]] owned and operated by the [[East Kentucky Cooperative]] near [[Somerset, Kentucky]]. It is actually closest to the smaller city of [[Burnside, Kentucky|Burnside]]. It is named after [[John Sherman Cooper]], a [[US Senator]] from [[Kentucky]].
